humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that the tumor classification is pT2(mult)N3aL1V0R0. This suggests that the patient has 4 or more axillary lymph nodes with metastases, which corresponds to N3 according to Rule 13.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The N stage is determined by the presence and extent of cancer spread to the lymph nodes. In this report, the T stage is pT2(mult), indicating a tumor size of 2.1-5.0 cm. The N3a in the TNM classification indicates that there are positive ipsilateral level III axillary lymph nodes. This is further supported by the 'L1' in the TNM classification, indicating 1-3 positive axillary lymph nodes. Therefore, the N stage from this report is N3.
